Premium Block Blobs are optimized for high-performance workloads that require low latency and high throughput. They are backed by SSD storage and are ideal for applications that frequently read and write data.

Unlike standard blob storage, premium block blobs are designed for workloads such as big data analytics, real-time processing, and high-performance computing.

For example, a media processing application that continuously uploads and processes large video files can benefit from premium block blobs.

A real-life use case is a streaming platform where content is uploaded and processed rapidly before being distributed globally.

Another example is machine learning pipelines that require fast access to training datasets.

Premium block blobs ensure consistent performance and reduced latency.
